list.abstract: TWICE，是JYP Entertainment于2015年10月20日推出的韩国女子演唱组合，由林娜琏、俞定延、平井桃（Momo）、凑崎纱夏（Sana）、朴志效、名井南（Mina）、金多贤、孙彩瑛、周子瑜9名成员组成。 2015年10月20日，TWICE发布首张迷你专辑《THE STORY BEGINS》，正式出道。12月，获得第17届Mnet亚洲音乐大奖最佳女子新人奖。2016年4月，发布第二张迷你专辑《PAGE TWO》。而后相继获得韩国金唱片大奖唱片部门新人赏 、Mnet亚洲音乐大奖最佳女子团体奖。2017年1月，TWICE首次获得韩国金唱片大奖音源部门大赏；10月，TWICE发行了首张团体正规专辑《Twicetagram》 。2018年12月，获得包括最佳女子团体在内的五项殊荣 。2019年12月31日，参演了NHK播出的音乐节目《第70回NHK红白歌合战》。2023年5月31日，在日本发行第十张单曲《Hare Hare》。11月28日，TWICE获得2023MAMA全球粉丝选择奖。 2024年2月23日，发行迷你13辑《With YOU-th》和主打曲《ONE SPARK》。
twice，英文单词，主要用作为副词，作为副词时译为“两次；两倍”。

yingyinNormal.en: This dough will need to prove twice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 面团需要醒两次。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes! There'd be twice as many parades!
yingyinNormal.zh: 会啊！会有两次夺冠游行！

yingyinNormal.en: Didn't you see Taylor Swift twice this month?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你这个月看了两次泰勒·斯威夫特的演唱会吧？{她的歌词以女孩恋爱/分手后的心情为主}

yingyinNormal.en: Why are you smiling? I had sex twice last night.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你为什么在笑？我昨晚做了两次爱。

yingyinNormal.en: But hear me, please, cousin. Twice my men and horses have ridden under your banner. Twice my men and two sons have fallen to the Chinese.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是请听我说，皇兄，我的人马跟着你征战了两次，两次，我的战士和我的两个儿子都战死在中原。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, well, a circumstance can happen twice and still be special.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，有些情况就算发生两次，仍然可以算作特殊。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait, so, you get to be my best man twice and I never get to be yours at all?
yingyinNormal.zh: 等一下，我让你当两次，你一次也不让我当？

yingyinNormal.en: I personally have shooed a homeless man away from peeing on that shrine twice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我亲自赶走了一个流浪汉不让他往神龛上撒尿，赶了两次啊。

yingyinNormal.en: You've been married twice? Yes. And another time after that. Boy I'm getting hungry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你结过两次婚？对，那个之后又结了一次，天啊，我饿了。

yingyinNormal.en: You managed to get the president of the United States on the phone not once, but twice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你已经两次打通了美国总统的电话。

yingyinNormal.en: How are you with pets? Well, I did take care of Sheldon for 15 years, and he only bit me twice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你跟宠物相处得好吗？我照顾了谢尔顿十五年，他只咬过我两次。

yingyinNormal.en: Calm down. Calm down. You set me up with the woman that I've dumped twice in the last five months.
yingyinNormal.zh: 冷静点？冷静？你竟撮合我与在五个月内被我甩掉两次的女人。

yingyinNormal.en: Just a sandwich? Look, I am 30 years old, okay? I'm gonna be divorced twice and I just got evicted.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过是个三明治？我今年30岁，已经离婚两次，还没地方可住。

yingyinNormal.en: Went to Sam's grave every day. Then twice a week. Then once a week. I sought out therapy for myself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 每天都去山姆的墓前，后来一周去两次，再后来一周一次，我还给自己找了心理医生。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't know what I was thinking. I mean, sleeping with him once, maybe you could understand, but twice?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不知道我在想什么，我是说，和他睡一次，我还能理解，但两次？

yingyinNormal.en: I shower twice a day and wash my hands as often as I can. Really? So do I. But you're a dentist. He's nuts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我每天洗两次澡，洗手无数次。真的？我也是。但你是牙科学生，他只是疯子。

yingyinNormal.en: This is Vegas man. People will pay to see freaky stuff. Okay, how much would you pay to see this hand twice?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里可是拉斯维加斯，大家就爱付钱看怪东西，好，你愿意付多少钱看两次这只手？

yingyinNormal.en: Mister I saved your life twice. Okay, I can't tell you how or when or why, but I have done shit that matters.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先生，我曾两次救过您的命，明白吗？我不能告诉你何时怎样，或为何，但我的确做了。

yingyinNormal.en: Uniform's forgotten. You have no voice? You were enlist? I was sir, Belleau Wood. Twice decorated. I see it, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 仅剩制服，无权发声？你参战了？是的，长官。在贝洛伍德。两次授勋，我看到的，先生。

yingyinNormal.en: No, I wasn't in a fire. And the word's "supposedly." What? You said that science is supposably really hard. Twice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没被火烧过。还有你刚刚提到恐怕。什么？你说科学课恐怕真的挺难的。说了两次呢。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: In an online forum post, Ahmed Bouchfaa responded that the brand holds sales of old stock for staff members <highlight>twice</highlight> a year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在一个在线论坛帖子中，Ahmed Bouchfaa回应说，该品牌每年为员工销售两次旧库存。

examination_example.sentence: One should think <highlight>twice</highlight> upon reading online comments and information, as they may be groundless and fictitious just to catch people's attention.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个人在阅读网上的评论和信息时应该三思，因为它们可能是毫无根据和虚构的，只是为了引起人们的注意。

数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全四级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Women are <highlight>twice</highlight> as likely to suffer from severe stress and anxiety as men, according to a 2016 study published.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据2016年发表的一项研究，女性遭受严重压力和焦虑的可能性是男性的两倍。

examination_example.sentence: Researchers concluded that those who just barely qualified for a grant were able to get <highlight>twice</highlight> as much money.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员得出结论，那些勉强有资格获得资助的人能够得到两倍的钱。

examination_example.sentence: Both words were used more frequently, and climate change was used nearly <highlight>twice</highlight> as often as global warming.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这两个词的使用频率都更高，气候变化的使用频率几乎是全球变暖的两倍。

examination_example.sentence: Think <highlight>twice</highlight> about new nutrition research findings.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对新的营养研究结果要慎重考虑。

examination_example.sentence: Americans eat about fifteen pounds of fish per person per year, but we eat <highlight>twice</highlight> as much fish in restaurants as at home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国人每年每人吃大约15磅的鱼，但是我们在餐馆里吃的鱼是在家里吃的两倍。

examination_example.sentence: We eat <highlight>twice</highlight> as much fish in restaurants as at home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们在餐馆里吃的鱼是在家里的两倍。

examination_example.sentence: The traffic signals generally don't flash the same length of green <highlight>twice</highlight> in a row, especially at rush hour.
